cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.AI, cs.DB 

This paper deals with learning representations of medical concepts using graph autoencoders and meta-embeddings. The use of machine learning techniques for clinical decision making and predictive modeling tasks falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for processing clinical notes, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of electronic health records (EHR) and the need to aggregate information from different modalities falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also involves the use of embeddings, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the representation and storage of medical data, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB).
